% [cabal-make](http://haskell.org/haskellwiki/Cabal-make) changes

## Version 0.5 ##

+  Added customization template: `my-cabal-make.inc`
+  hasktags now uses `$(sources)`
+  Added  [PanDoc](http://sophos.berkeley.edu/macfarlane/pandoc/) rules &
   `pandocs` target.  Makes [CHANGES.html](CHANGES.html) from [CHANGES](CHANGES).
+  Added [makefile](makefile)

## Version 0.4 ##

+  Changed handling of `top-src-dir`.  Now contains its own trailing "/", or
   empty if source starts in main directory.

## Version 0.3 ##

Contributions from Jean-Philippe Bernardy:

+  Emacs-mode hint at top of `cabal-make.inc`
+  Make the source-directory configurable
+  Allow to customize HsColour path
+  Allow extra configuration options

## Version 0.2 ##

+  Fixed potentially catastrophic bug: "tmp-dir" vs "temp-dir"
+  Added doc-clean target and remote doc cleaning
+  Added CHANGES file
